Structured Queury Language:
- the way we communicate to databases
- uses clauses to create a statement

Basic Concepts in SQL:
- SELECT -> choose columns to display
- FROM -> choose table where you're looking at
- WHERE -> filter data (rows)
- GROUP BY -> allows you to group your data's in rows
- HAVING BY -> filter GROUPED rows (NOT RAW datas)
- ORDER BY -> allows you to sort your data

ADDITIONAL
- LIMIT -> allows you to put a specific number of data that will be displayed
- COUNT -> number of data's that meets the condition specified
- DISTINCT -> allows you to view a unique value (distinct)
